'''''Culture of Death''''' is a [[rhetorical device]] used in contemporary political discourse in the [[United States]]. It is used to equate the target with the [[T-4 Euthanasia Program|euthanasia programs]] of [[Nazi Germany]]. "Culture of death" has been used during debates regarding the maintenance or removal of feeding tubes for medical patient [[Terri Schiavo]] in the United States. So used, the term implies that those who do not support the reinsertion of her feeding tube are part of a "culture of death".

''Culture of Death'' may also refer to cultures which gloified or worshiped death.

